19 SECTION 7. G.S. 163-230.1(e1), as amended by Section 3A.4(f) of S.L. 2024-57,
20 reads as rewritten:
21 "(e1) Curable Deficiencies. – If a container-return envelope contains a curable deficiency,
22 the county board shall promptly notify the voter of the deficiency and the manner in which the
23 voter may cure the deficiency. Curable deficiencies are deficiencies that can be cured with
24 supplemental documentation or attestation provided by the voter, including when any of the
25 following occurs:
26 (1) The voter did not sign the voter certification as required by
27 G.S. 163-231(a)(4).
28 (2) The voter signed the application in the wrong place on the application.
29 (3) The voter failed to include with the container-return envelope a photocopy of
30 identification described in G.S. 163-166.16(a) or an affidavit as described in
31 G.S. 163-166.16(d)(1), (d)(2), or (d)(3), as required by subsection (f1) of this
32 section.
33 The identification of the two persons witnessing the casting of the absentee ballot in
34 accordance with G.S. 163-231(a) is not a curable deficiency. Any container-return envelope with
35 a curable deficiency that is transmitted to the county board shall be considered timely if cure
36 documentation is received no later than 12:00 5:00 P.M. on the third fifth business day after the
37 election. Cure documentation may be transmitted via email to the county board if the deficiency
38 is one described in subdivision (3) of this subsection. The notification of voters regarding curable
39 deficiencies is an administrative task that may be performed by county board staff and is not
40 required to be performed at an absentee meeting as provided for in subsection (f) of this section.
41 The voter shall be notified of curable deficiencies by mail, and by telephone or email if the
42 telephone number or email address was provided by the voter on the request form for absentee
43 ballots."
44 SECTION 8.(a) G.S. 163-278.9 reads as rewritten:
45 "§ 163-278.9. Statements filed with State Board.
46 (a) Except as provided in G.S. 163-278.10A, the treasurer of each candidate and of each
47 political committee shall file with the State Board under certification of the treasurer as true and
48 correct to the best of the knowledge of that officer the following reports:
49 …
50 (2) 48-Hour Report. – A political committee, political party or affiliated party
51 committee that receives a contribution or transfer of funds shall disclose
Page 4 House Bill 958-First Edition

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 within 48 hours of receipt a contribution or transfer of one two thousand
2 dollars ($1,000) ($2,000) or more received before an election but after the
3 period covered by the last report due before that election. The disclosure shall
4 be by report to the State Board identifying the source and amount of the funds.
5 The State Board shall specify the form and manner of making the report,
6 including the reporting of in-kind contributions. The State Board shall
7 increase the dollar amount of the reporting threshold effective each election
8 cycle beginning the period from January 1 of an odd-numbered year through
9 December 31 of the next even-numbered year based on the Consumer Price
10 Index as provided in G.S. 163-278.13(b). The State Board shall set the revised
11 threshold in October of the even-numbered year, publish the revised threshold
12 in the North Carolina Register, and notify the Revisor of Statutes who shall
13 adjust the dollar amount in this subdivision.
14 …
15 (a1) Subdivision (a)(2) of this section shall not apply to any candidate campaign
16 committee, as defined by G.S. 163-278.38Z, in a primary election in which the candidate is
17 unopposed on that ballot.
18 …."
19 SECTION 8.(b) G.S. 163-278.9A reads as rewritten:
20 "§ 163-278.9A. Statements filed by referendum committees.
21 (a) The treasurer of each referendum committee shall file under verification with the
22 Board the following reports:
23 …
24 (3) 48-Hour Report. – A referendum committee that receives a contribution or
25 transfer of funds shall disclose within 48 hours of receipt a contribution or
26 transfer of one two thousand dollars ($1,000) ($2,000) or more received before
27 a referendum but after the period covered by the last report due before that
28 referendum. The disclosure shall be by report to the State Board of Elections
29 identifying the source and amount of such funds. The State Board of Elections
30 shall specify the form and manner of making the report, including the
31 reporting of in-kind contributions. The State Board shall increase the dollar
32 amount of the reporting threshold effective each election cycle beginning the
33 period from January 1 of an odd-numbered year through December 31 of the
34 next even-numbered year based on the Consumer Price Index as provided in
35 G.S. 163-278.13(b). The State Board shall set the revised threshold in October
36 of the even-numbered year, publish the revised threshold in the North Carolina
37 Register, and notify the Revisor of Statutes who shall adjust the dollar amount
38 in this subdivision.
39 …
40 (a1) Subdivision (a)(3) of this section shall not apply to any candidate campaign
41 committee, as defined by G.S. 163-278.38Z, in a primary election in which the candidate is
42 unopposed on that ballot.
43 …."
44 SECTION 8.(c) No earlier than October 1, 2025, the State Board of Elections shall
45 adjust the thresholds imposed by G.S. 163-278.9(a)(2) and G.S. 163-278.9A(a)(3), as enacted by
46 this section, effective for the election cycle beginning January 1, 2027.
47 SECTION 9. Except as otherwise provided, this act is effective when it becomes law
48 and applies to elections held on or after that date.
